This memorandum, issued by President Barack Obama on October 18, 2015, discusses the implementation of the Joint Comprehensive Plan of Action (JCPOA) of July 14, 2015. It states that on Adoption Day, all participants of the JCPOA, including the United States, are to make the necessary preparations for implementing their commitments. The Secretary of State is directed to take action with respect to waivers of relevant statutory sanctions, subject to confirmation by the Secretary of State that Iran has implemented the nuclear-related measures specified in the JCPOA. The memorandum also directs the relevant departments to take additional measures to ensure the prompt and effective implementation of the U.S. commitments in accordance with U.S. law, including steps to give effect to the U.S. commitments with respect to sanctions. The Secretary of State is authorized and directed to publish this memorandum in the Federal Register.